The Just-In-Time Adaptive Decoder Engine (Jade) project is a new dynamic decoder based on the Low Level Virtual Machine (LLVM), fully compliant with MPEG RVC paradigm.
The Jade executable can dynamically instantiate several RVC decoder descriptions produced by the LLVM back-end of Orcc.
The JadeToolBox is an executable which allows an optimized generation of a proprietary Video Tool Library.

Reader is invited to go to: http://orcc.sourceforge.net for finding more information about Jade.

Input stimuli of decoders are available at: https://sourceforge.net/projects/orcc/files/Sequences/

An LLVM representation of the Video Tools Library must be downloaded at: https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/Jade.VTL.1.0.RC.zip
This VTL can also be generated by the LLVM backend of Orcc

************************************************************************************************
                                         Quick start
************************************************************************************************
Binaries of Jade version can be downloaded at:
(Win32) https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/binaries/Jade_1.0_win32.exe
(Win64) https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/binaries/Jade_1.0_win64.exe
(Win32) https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/binaries/Jade_1.0_win32.exe
(Linux32) https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/binaries/Jade_1.0_linux_32
(Linux64) https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/binaries/Jade_1.0_linux_64
(Mac64) https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/orcc/Jade/1.0/binaries/Jade_1.0_mac_64

Launch the following command line:
./Jade -xdf ($XDF_FILE).xdf -i ($INPUT_SEQ).m4v -L ($VTL_FOLDER) -O3

where
	XDF_FILE : The location of a network (for i.: Top_RVC.xdf for MPEG-4 SP)
	INPUT_SEQ : The location of the input stimulus (for i.: hit001.m4v for MPEG-4 SP)
	VTL_FOLDER :  The path of the VTL (for i.: ($home)/Jade/VTL/)

	
************************************************************************************************
                                       Structure of the project
************************************************************************************************
The Jade project is structured as follow :
- src contains the source of the Jade project
- build the compiled tools for several operating systems (Windows, Linux and Mac Os)
- doc contains all the documentation of the src project
- VTL is the folder where the Video Tool Library as normalized in MPEG-C must be set.

The use of Jade is detailed in the enclosed COMMAND file.


************************************************************************************************
                                           Compile Jade
************************************************************************************************

The compilation of this project requires the following libraries:
- SDL-1.2.14 (http://www.libsdl.org)
- LLVM 2.9 (http://llvm.org)

The project is based on the Cross-platform Make CMake (at least 2.6), which can be found at http://www.cmake.org.

If you are using Visual Studio 2010, 2008 or 2005, the two first libraries can be found in runtime zip file. Simply run cmake.bat to automatically set environment variables.

More information about Jade compilation can be found at http://orcc.sourceforge.net/drupal/?q=CompileJade.

